^B@2^Y@3^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|First, let's talk about the bidding. I recommend playing DONT over 1NT openers with an appropriate hand. East has an appropriate hand. Playing DONT, there are 2 choices of what to bid with the hand. If you decide to treat the hand as a single suited club hand, you can double, showing a single suit (playing DONT). And if you decide to treat it as a 2 suited hand, you can bid 2C showing clubs and another suit. I would choose 2C, mostly because I want to get my club suit in. In any case I would definitely compete over 1N with the East hand.|
PG| ***** 20 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^^Y@3*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Now, as to the play. The club lead was fine. As to whether East should shift. Unless there is a good reason to think diamonds is the appropriate shift, that would be my last choice of what to play at trick 2. If you want to play a "passive" defense, not giving anything away, a second club is fine. Many people are reluctant to play a suit that declarer can ruff, but there is no reason to be afraid of doing that. At worst it gives nothing away (as on this hand), and sometimes (on other hands) it shortens declarer's trumps prematurely. So, never be reluctant to give declarer a ruff unless there is a better play.|
PG| ***** 21 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^Y@3^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Now, with East's hand and the @HQ in dummy, I would lead the @HJ at trick 2. Some people play that with a singleton in dummy, West should do a suit preference discard. If you play that, then a low club discard would be a suit preference for diamonds, and a high club a suit preference for hearts. And East tells me that is what was assumed, which accounts for the diamond shift. However, I don't particularly care for that signaling. On many hands, such as this one, West has preference for neither suit.|
PG| ***** 22 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^Y@3^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Next, let me address how to play Qxx opposite Axx. Many students play the Queen, as Sandy did but I call that a "practice finesse." The reason for that is, even if it works, it does not gain you a trick. The only way to legitimately take two tricks in the suit is to lead low towards the Queen and hope East has the King. Leading the Queen guarantees two heart losers against proper defense.|
PG| ***** 23 ***** |


