^B@2^Y@3^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Many would open my hand in 3rd seat, because opening light is a popular approach. However, I am strictly a rule of 20 person myself. I find that if I open light, particularly with many of my aggressive partners, we end up getting too high. So, my style is only to open in all seats if I meet the rule of 20. I am not saying that is what you should do, but just that is what I do.  I have discussed this with Marty Bergen, and he respectfully but violently disagrees with me. But I have had good results, particularly on pass outs, so I am sticking to my guns on this issue :).|
