^B@2^Y@3^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Now, lets talk about Marty Bergen's OBAR approach. What Marty Bergen recommends is, if it goes 1X-P-2X, the direct seat should strain to balance as well. OBAR means "Over Opponent Bid and Raise." He says you can consider any bid by the direct opponent as a "pre-balance." So, a suit is simply a suit, double is takeout, and he plays 2NT as a minor suit takeout bid, which is the perfect bid for Marge's hand.|
